1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:11,600
<i> Are you looking for me?</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,400
<i>Perfect timing, I'm going
to use my new weapon.</i>

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> That's from there.</i>

4
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Maybe it's Enriquez.</i>

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:22,900
<i> Enriquez!</i>

6
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:23,800
<i> Enriquez!</i>

7
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:26,333
<i> Some inmates have escaped</i>

8
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:29,700
<i>and are currently on the loose
here in Calabari.</i>

9
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,633
<i>They'll be going around,
and then...</i>

10
00:00:31,767 --> 00:00:33,600
<i> Faye!</i>

11
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:34,333
<i> Enriquez!</i>

12
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:34,833
<i> Sir...</i>

13
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> Are you okay?</i>

14
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:36,500
<i> I got into a fight, Sir.</i>

15
00:00:36,633 --> 00:00:38,467
<i>You'd better wait for backup
to arrive.</i>

16
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,067
<i>I'll look for the other inmates.</i>

17
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:42,900
<i>If Jako isn't the new supplier
of the pimple patch drugs,</i>

18
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:43,933
<i> then who is it?</i>

19
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:45,600
<i>All I know is,
Monty has a girlfriend.</i>

20
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>Babe, if I get caught,
I'll go to jail.</i>

21
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:49,633
<i> You're just here!</i>

22
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:51,167
<i>I've been looking for you
for a while!</i>

23
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:51,933
<i> Why?</i>

24
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:52,967
<i> Something happened to Faye!</i>

25
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,967
<i> Don't run! I'll shoot you!</i>

26
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:56,433
<i> I won't fight back.</i>

27
00:00:59,033 --> 00:01:00,333
<i> You're dead now.</i>

28
00:01:01,367 --> 00:01:02,433
<i> Go ahead, try it!</i>

29
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>You're going to fall straight
into hell, Mando!</i>

30
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,367
<i> Bok...</i>

31
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:07,100
<i>- Help me, Bok.
- Bok, it's not that serious.</i>

32
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,533
<i>- Let's go!
- Bok...</i>

33
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:09,667
<i> Who's behind this?</i>

34
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,700
<i>Mando Garrido, also known
as Mandong Warak, Sir,</i>

35
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:12,933
<i> and Romel Salvador.</i>

36
00:01:13,067 --> 00:01:13,967
<i>What's the update about Mando
and the others?</i>

37
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,133
<i> Do you know where he is?</i>

38
00:01:15,267 --> 00:01:16,333
<i> Not yet.</i>

39
00:01:16,467 --> 00:01:18,367
<i>That's why I'll call the chief
and get an update.</i>

40
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:23,767
Major, what's the update there?

41
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:24,833
Hello, Mayor?

42
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,633
The situation here is stable.

43
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:30,500
The other police officers
have already chased down

44
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:32,133
the escaped prisoners.

45
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:34,300
How are our police officers?

46
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,700
How's Bobby?

47
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:37,933
<i> They're okay, Mayor.</i>

48
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:41,033
Everyone from Police Station 12
is here.

49
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,133
Sergeant Enriquez is safe.

50
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:45,600
Okay, Major.

51
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:47,100
I'll go there.

52
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,667
Thank you very much.

53
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,833
Okay, Mayor.

54
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:07,633
Sophia, you don't drink, right?

55
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:11,533
I will do whatever I want,
Joaquin.

56
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:12,433
Why?

57
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:14,333
Are you the only one who can?

58
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:18,000
No one's stopping you
when you do what you want,

59
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:20,233
even if it hurts me.

60
00:02:20,367 --> 00:02:22,667
It's like I'm not your wife!

61
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:25,467
Sophia,

62
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,533
don't you get tired?

63
00:02:26,667 --> 00:02:27,367
No!

64
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:31,700
Sophia...

65
00:02:33,233 --> 00:02:34,567
I'm old already.

66
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,533
I wish...

67
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:41,567
Before I leave this world,

68
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,467
I wish I could be a father
to my daughter.

69
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:48,833
I love my family.

70
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,733
But...

71
00:02:51,367 --> 00:02:54,367
I wish I could love
Bobby as my child, too.

72
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,967
I hope you understand me.

73
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,200
Hello, Chief.

74
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:51,600
Garcia and I are still
in the ER.

75
00:03:51,733 --> 00:03:53,500
I'm still waiting for him
to be discharged.

76
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,533
Conde, when Garcia's
condition is stable,

77
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:56,600
come back here, okay?

78
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:57,533
Yes, Sir.

79
00:03:57,667 --> 00:03:58,600
By the way...

80
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:01,733
How are the escapees, Chief?

81
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:02,900
Have they all been caught?

82
00:04:03,033 --> 00:04:04,733
There's no confirmed report yet,

83
00:04:04,867 --> 00:04:07,467
but Enriquez and Noble
are staying here.

84
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,800
You can ask them for an update.

85
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:09,900
Yes, Sir.

86
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:13,100
Sir...

87
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,267
can I talk to Enriquez?

88
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:22,800
It's Conde. He wants to talk
to you.

89
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:26,267
Hello, Sir?

90
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:27,100
Bobby!

91
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,833
How are you? Are you okay?

92
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:32,533
Are you hurt?

93
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:35,400
No, Sir, I'm okay.

94
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:38,100
I'll go ahead.
I have to get back to work.

95
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,433
Okay.

96
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:51,400
Enriquez?

97
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:52,667
Yes, Sir?

98
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,767
My phone.

99
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:56,400
Sorry, Sir.

100
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:59,033
You guys take care
of this matter.

101
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,367
Conde and Garcia are still
at the hospital.

102
00:05:02,533 --> 00:05:03,300
Yes, Sir.

103
00:05:32,700 --> 00:05:35,700
Guys, let's hurry up.
Let's go see Faye.

104
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:37,567
Do you know where Faye is?

105
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,167
I can't contact her.

106
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:41,633
That's the thing,
she was taken to the clinic.

107
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:44,067
She was wearing a pimple patch
earlier!

108
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:44,767
What?

109
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,567
How did that happen?
Where did it come from?

110
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,967
I don't know! She just suddenly
collapsed!

111
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:53,033
Come on, let's go see her.

112
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,633
I can't come with you.
I have to go somewhere.

113
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,033
Sorry.

114
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,733
- Let's go, where's the clinic?
- Let's go! There!

115
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:02,467
Let's go.

116
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,467
Coffee?

117
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,500
Thank you.

118
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:12,267
That Markus is a fool.

119
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,867
Even though he's dead,
he's still harassing me.

120
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,033
Look...

121
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,667
because of him,
I'm still hiding.

122
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,433
The police are still watching
my every move.

123
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:24,100
You answer that.

124
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:27,700
Boss...

125
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,800
What's the update about Mando?

126
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:31,700
Well, nothing yet, Boss.

127
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:35,233
There are people who escaped,
but it's not confirmed who.

128
00:06:35,367 --> 00:06:36,933
Call Robles.

129
00:06:37,067 --> 00:06:38,833
Maybe he knows something.

130
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:41,133
Copy, Boss. I'll ask.

131
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,367
<i> Boss...</i>

132
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,967
it's not that I'm getting
ahead of you

133
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,667
or questioning your abilities.

134
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:49,067
But why are you helping
that guy?

135
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:53,333
You know, his old-school
approach won't work anymore.

136
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:56,700
Plus, that guy is crazy, Boss.

137
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:58,967
Because he never fails.

138
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:02,100
He never failed at anything
I asked him to do.

139
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:10,633
Wait a minute,
I'll call you back.

140
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:12,833
That's it.

141
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:15,700
Mom?

142
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:18,500
Glen, I'm at the university
clinic.

143
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:20,200
Faye collapsed!

144
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:23,333
They said it's because
of the pimple patch drugs.

145
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,167
What?

146
00:07:25,367 --> 00:07:26,400
Where did she get it?

147
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:30,367
I don't know, and I can't even
talk to her properly!

148
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:32,800
Glen, can you do me a favor,
please?

149
00:07:32,933 --> 00:07:36,033
Call your dad because I can't
contact him, okay?

150
00:07:36,167 --> 00:07:37,467
Maybe he's still in a meeting.

151
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,933
Yeah, okay.

152
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:41,000
Mom, please update me
about Faye.

153
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,967
Okay?

154
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,100
Cecilia...

155
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,533
Doc Cecilia...

156
00:07:57,667 --> 00:07:59,200
Bok, I have to go.

157
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,433
We need to find and catch
everyone who escaped,

158
00:08:01,567 --> 00:08:02,967
especially Mando.

159
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:03,800
Is that so?

160
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:04,933
Bok...

161
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:09,200
is it okay for you
to call Doc Cecilia?

162
00:08:11,133 --> 00:08:12,067
What should I say?

163
00:08:13,167 --> 00:08:15,833
Tell her I got wounded.
Oh, no...

164
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:17,667
I was hacked to death.

165
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:21,000
Then I was at a 50/50 chance,
fighting for my life.

166
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,067
Then while I was fighting
for my life,

167
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,800
I was screaming her name.

168
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:27,100
Oh, no, no. I was mentioning
her name.

169
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:28,567
"Cecilia..."

170
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:31,200
That's it, something like that,
to make her pity me, okay?

171
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,933
Okay, I'll call Doc Cecilia,

172
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:37,467
but I'll tell you that
you weren't hurt by the axe.

173
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:41,633
You were hurt more when you
found out she had a boyfriend.

174
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:43,700
Bok, don't say that to her!
That's true, but it's not nice.

175
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,433
The "50/50 chance" one is
better. Like this, "Cecilia!"

176
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,367
Bok!

177
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:20,267
Conde!

178
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,667
That's the sound of a gunshot.

179
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,567
Tonyo...

180
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,233
Move!

181
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:48,067
Move aside!

182
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,367
Move!

183
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:58,200
Oh, my husband!
Help! Help! Help us!

184
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:05,733
Bok...

185
00:10:07,733 --> 00:10:09,767
Bok!

186
00:10:22,667 --> 00:10:23,767
Help!

187
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,567
Help us!

188
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,400
Hurry up!

189
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:50,933
"Are you okay, Bobby?
Are you hurt?"

190
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,333
I don't want to talk to him.
He's annoying.

191
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:01,967
Hello, Sir?

192
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,267
<i> Hello, Enriquez.</i>

193
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,867
<i>Tonyo was shot here at the
hospital by Mandong Warak.</i>

194
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,133
What?

195
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:09,133
Okay, I'll tell the chief.

196
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,500
We'll go there.

197
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,333
It's boss again.

198
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:22,500
Boss, you called again.
Did you miss us, Boss?

199
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,500
What happened?

200
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:27,633
How did the drugs
get to my sister?

201
00:11:27,767 --> 00:11:29,200
Did you sell that to her?

202
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:31,633
No, Boss. Maybe she got them
from someone else.

203
00:11:31,767 --> 00:11:33,533
Boss, if she has a classmate
who's using them,

204
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:35,100
we have no control over that.

205
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:37,233
Yes, Boss.

206
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:41,267
Or maybe Faye is a user,
you just don't know.

207
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:42,533
Shut up!

208
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:44,467
My sister is not an addict!

209
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:47,667
You know, if you were here,
I might have hit you.

210
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:50,833
I'm sorry, Boss.

211
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:51,600
Glen.

212
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:54,233
Who are you talking to?

213
00:11:57,700 --> 00:11:58,900
Nothing, Dad.

214
00:11:59,033 --> 00:12:01,400
We just couldn't hear
each other.

215
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:05,400
Be careful when you're talking
to the boss.

216
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:09,367
He may seem nice, but he
no longer has no soul.

217
00:12:17,333 --> 00:12:19,167
By the way, mom was calling you.

218
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:20,767
She said she couldn't
contact you.

219
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:23,633
We had an argument earlier.

220
00:12:23,767 --> 00:12:25,300
I don't want to talk to her.

221
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,700
Dad, he's calling
because of Faye.

222
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:30,900
Oh, why?

223
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:33,533
Faye collapsed because
of the pimple patch drugs.

224
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:34,433
What?

225
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,567
Faye!

226
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:44,033
Hey!

227
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:46,833
What took you so long?

228
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:48,767
I've been waiting for you.

229
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:50,900
What did you do?

230
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:52,767
Nothing.

231
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:57,600
Faye, where did you get
the pimple patch?

232
00:12:57,733 --> 00:12:59,233
We've been asking her.

233
00:12:59,367 --> 00:13:01,967
She can't answer directly.

234
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:05,167
Sir Chito, do you know
those two,

235
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:09,967
especially that guy,
they're hiding something!

236
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:12,133
They're hiding something!

237
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,000
You have a crush on me, right?

238
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:16,167
Hey.

239
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,900
He has a crush on me!

240
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:19,367
Admit it!

241
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,867
You have a crush on me, right?

242
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,600
He has a crush on me!

243
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:25,867
He really has a crush on me,
Mom.

244
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,833
Auntie, maybe she's still high

245
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:29,933
because she had two pimple
patches on earlier.

246
00:13:30,067 --> 00:13:31,167
- That's why she's like that.
- I'm not...

247
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:33,600
He really has a crush on me.

248
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:36,200
How can this happen
inside the campus?

249
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,533
Is there a drug dealer here?

250
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,133
I'll get to the bottom of this,
Ma'am.

251
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:45,467
Ma'am, when Faye calms down,

252
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,833
that's when we'll know who gave
her the pimple patch drugs.

253
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:57,500
Garcia!

254
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:00,067
Where is Conde?

255
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,900
He's inside.

256
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:02,900
Let's go.

257
00:14:05,567 --> 00:14:08,033
Sir, based on the x-ray
and CT scan,

258
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:10,400
there are no vital organs
affected.

259
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,467
You'll be fine.

260
00:14:13,433 --> 00:14:13,933
Doc...

261
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,400
How is Conde?

262
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:19,000
Based on his X-ray
and CT scan results,

263
00:14:19,133 --> 00:14:21,067
there are no vital organs
that were hit.

264
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,300
We just need to prepare
the OR first,

265
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:24,767
then we'll do the operation.

266
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:28,367
Doc, how long
will his recovery be?

267
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:29,867
It'll only be a few days,

268
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,800
just don't let him move too much
because the wound might open up.

269
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,067
Thank you, Doc.

270
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,267
Okay, I'll just prepare the OR.

271
00:14:42,533 --> 00:14:43,600
Conde, how are you?

272
00:14:45,767 --> 00:14:47,867
Did Mando escape?

273
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:51,433
Yes, Conde, with the other two.

274
00:14:51,567 --> 00:14:53,967
So there are three
fugitives now.

275
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:58,400
When I get out, Chief,
I'll help with the manhunt.

276
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:00,533
Didn't you hear
what the doc said?

277
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,967
He said you need to rest.

278
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:06,533
Don't move too much,
so the wound doesn't reopen.

279
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:08,600
And you still want to join
the manhunt operation?

280
00:15:08,733 --> 00:15:10,133
Oh my.

281
00:15:10,267 --> 00:15:12,467
That's right, Bok,
just rest for now.

282
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,733
Get well soon, okay?

283
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:18,400
Conde, many police
officers were involved...

284
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:22,000
but don't worry, we'll take care
of it.

285
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:24,933
We won't let Mando escape.

286
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:27,700
Garcia, come with me.

287
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:31,633
Let's call the press
to help find Mando.

288
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:33,067
- Let's go!
- Yes, Sir.

289
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,333
Bok, sad face.

290
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,767
Why would you still join
the manhunt operation?

291
00:15:48,567 --> 00:15:51,867
You've been hit by a bullet.
You're already in the hospital.

292
00:15:54,467 --> 00:15:57,033
You're not a robot, okay?
You're a human.

293
00:15:57,167 --> 00:15:59,100
You're wounded right now.

294
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:04,400
Enriquez, I can hear you.

295
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:06,400
Can you please say it louder?

296
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:10,433
Thank you very much
for visiting me.

297
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:17,033
Can you promise me...

298
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:20,433
that you won't join them in the
search for Mando anymore?

299
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:22,200
Leave that to someone else.

300
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,067
Where's my mom?

301
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,833
She just went out for a moment.

302
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:36,500
She can't contact your dad.

303
00:16:37,767 --> 00:16:38,833
Faye...

304
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:41,433
those pimple patch drugs
from earlier,

305
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,667
where did you get them?

306
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:45,767
In Anika's makeup bag.

307
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:47,067
Anika?

308
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,500
That's why she was in a hurry
to leave.

309
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:52,200
Was she the one I bumped into
earlier?

310
00:16:52,333 --> 00:16:53,267
Sorry.

311
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:58,400
Do you know where she lives?

312
00:16:58,533 --> 00:16:59,700
I know.

313
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:01,300
I'll come with you.

314
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:18,700
Babe...

315
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,200
Answer the phone, please...

316
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,900
What's with you, Babe?

317
00:17:28,033 --> 00:17:30,433
Why aren't you answering?

318
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:32,367
She's really stubborn.

319
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,433
I said I'm the only one
who can call.

320
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:43,500
Bro...

321
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,300
You have 2...

322
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,167
Sir...

323
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,033
Sir...

324
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:57,367
Sir, can I go to the CR?

325
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,267
You're always going to the CR.

326
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,600
Just bear with it.

327
00:18:04,567 --> 00:18:05,933
Sir.

328
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:07,267
Sir...

329
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,100
- I couldn't hold it anymore.
- I told you to bear with it!

330
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:09,900
Sit down!

331
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,500
I don't know what to do.

332
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,433
Hello, Anika?

333
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:32,667
Hello, Jhem?

334
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:33,800
I'm so sorry.

335
00:18:33,933 --> 00:18:37,333
I didn't know Faye was going
to mess with my bag.

336
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:40,233
Anika, are you in our favorite
hangout place?

337
00:18:40,367 --> 00:18:41,567
Yes.

338
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:44,933
I'm nervous.
What happened to Faye?

339
00:18:45,067 --> 00:18:46,200
She's okay.

340
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:47,500
Listen.

341
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:50,633
Bill and Vic are going to see
you now. They're with Jade.

342
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:53,133
What?

343
00:18:53,267 --> 00:18:54,267
Why?

344
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,567
I don't know either.

345
00:18:55,733 --> 00:19:00,500
But Faye already said that they
got the pimple patch from you.

346
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:03,000
Oh my God. I need to get out
of here.

347
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:04,333
I need to get out of here.

348
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:05,433
No!

349
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:06,400
No!

350
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,900
You can't escape this.

351
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:09,100
What do you mean?

352
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:11,167
You can't hide this from them!

353
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,400
<i> Okay, look.</i>

354
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:13,767
<i> I have this feeling that...</i>

355
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:15,700
Bill and Vic are undercover
agents.

356
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,600
I think that's not
their real names.

357
00:19:18,733 --> 00:19:21,200
And then they just suddenly
showed up at our school.

358
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:23,867
Then I heard them talking
earlier,

359
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,733
like they were really looking
for the supplier

360
00:19:25,867 --> 00:19:26,967
of the pimple patch.

361
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:29,533
You're not putting this on me,
Jhem.

362
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:33,233
I bought the pimple patch
from you, right?

363
00:19:33,367 --> 00:19:34,867
Maybe you forgot about that.

364
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,733
That's what I'm saying.

365
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:39,567
They can't know that you got it
from me.

366
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:41,100
What do you want me to do?

367
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,600
Wait for them to grill me, Jhem?

368
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:44,867
Okay, wait.

369
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,233
This is easy, Anika.

370
00:19:47,967 --> 00:19:51,900
You can tell them that you just
got the pimple patch from...

371
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:53,400
from the store.

372
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,200
A product sample,
something like that.

373
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,933
Product sample?

374
00:19:58,067 --> 00:19:59,367
Who do you think
would believe that?

375
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,267
Tell me, do you believe that?

376
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,133
Yeah!

377
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:07,133
Just stick to the plan, okay?
And everything will be fine.

378
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:31,467
Good job, Enriquez.

379
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:34,600
I haven't even been able
to thank you yet.

380
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,867
How can you say it's a good job

381
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,600
when Lieutenant Conde
is in danger?

382
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:44,567
If you hadn't responded sooner,
more people might have escaped.

383
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:48,167
Enriquez, I'm not stupid
or blind.

384
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:51,100
But I don't know what happened
to you and Conde.

385
00:20:51,233 --> 00:20:53,267
Sometimes, you guys are like
cats and dogs.

386
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,433
But despite everything,

387
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:57,867
I have high confidence
in the two of you

388
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:01,567
because I know you have
each other's backs.

389
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,567
So, don't worry...

390
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,467
Conde can handle that.

391
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:12,333
- Sir.
- Garcia.

392
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:16,433
Sir, how is Lieutenant Conde?

393
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:18,300
Conde's condition is stable now.

394
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,233
It's good that his organs
weren't hit.

395
00:21:21,533 --> 00:21:25,900
It's also good that Mando
isn't good at using a gun.

396
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:27,900
I think he only knows
how to use an axe.

397
00:21:28,033 --> 00:21:29,200
That's good news, Garcia.

398
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:31,867
At least Conde will recover.

399
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,067
It's Warden.

400
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,367
Just a moment.

401
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,367
Hello?

402
00:21:48,333 --> 00:21:49,400
Enriquez...

403
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,533
Conde is okay.

404
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:54,433
Why, Sir? Am I saying something?

405
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:57,500
Even if you don't say anything,
I can feel it.

406
00:21:57,633 --> 00:22:00,033
You're worried about him
to the bone.

407
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,700
It's nice to feel that way,
isn't it?

408
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,500
That someone is worried
about you.

409
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:08,933
Meanwhile...

410
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:15,400
I got axed and everything,
but no one still cares about me.

411
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:23,633
I feel like no one will visit me
here or even check on me.

412
00:22:23,767 --> 00:22:24,633
Eric...

413
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,233
Doc...

414
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,633
Cecilia...

415
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:35,333
I knew it, you can't ignore me.

416
00:22:36,667 --> 00:22:38,367
I just wanted to check
on all of you.

417
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:41,900
I heard a lot of people
were hurt by what happened.

418
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:56,433
<i>Finally, I got my revenge
on you, Conde.</i>

419
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:02,900
What happened at the hospital
was terrible, wasn't it?

420
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,533
A policeman was shot.

421
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:06,833
It's a good thing he wasn't
seriously wounded.

422
00:23:06,967 --> 00:23:10,267
Well, I heard he's undergoing
surgery right now.

423
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,567
I hope he survives.

424
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:13,533
That's true.

425
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,100
<i>You really are an animal, Conde.</i>

426
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:24,367
<i> How did you survive?</i>

427
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:28,467
<i> I won't stop until I kill you.</i>

428
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:32,433
I might not be able to join you
on our mission.

429
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,367
I'll contact a colleague.

430
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,733
He used to work as an undercover
agent under Lieutenant Conde.

431
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:37,933
Corporal Allen Matibag.

432
00:23:38,067 --> 00:23:40,267
Vince De Leon,
professional undercover.

433
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,200
Come with me if you don't
want to get in trouble.

434
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:42,933
Come on, let's follow.

435
00:23:43,067 --> 00:23:44,033
Come on.

436
00:23:44,167 --> 00:23:46,167
Let me know when the supplier
is caught, okay?

437
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:49,000
I'll make sure that
they will all rot in prison.

438
00:23:49,133 --> 00:23:53,800
Enriquez, just let them search
for Mando.

439
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,467
Please assign Mando over to me.

440
00:23:55,633 --> 00:23:56,633
I'll take care of him.

441
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:58,867
Bobby, do you need backup?
